text: Joshua and Hui Hee were extremely patient and diligent with handling my order of 24 cups of coffee. Most importantly, Joshua was cheerful and maintained a smile throughout!

So cool...

At my desk on the 17th floor of Centennial Tower I use the Starbucks app to order a coffee. Then I go down to collect it. I see an empty seat and as soon as I sit down the barista calls my name!

And as it was the first time I used the app I got 50% off!

This location was also recently renovated so it's got nice chairs etc

The food and drinks are the same in any of the Starbucks branches, but it's the service and the people that makes this a 5 star experience every time. I come here quite often and it didn't take Leon very long to not only remember me, my favourite drink but also my name!

Staffs here were the nicest among the many sbuxs I had been in Singapore. They were always friendly and made the drinks right. Location was really calm and quiet in the mornings. Most importantly, the place was always clean! Perhaps need some signs to ask the patrons to clean up the table after eating/drinking. Cleaning after people is not any baristaâ€™s job.

I love the overall here! Is middle of this mall Millennia Walk! This is one of the few Starbucks on my list now here in SG to stay as there are more power sockets so far!
Thanks to the night staff
Male Supervisor I can't remember his name, Fauzee (I can't spell his name) (7/9 aftr 2100 shift). He was rather patience to try on for me to c if the limited edition tumbler will cause any leakage when filled with water.
